title: Killing Eve [Spoilers for Episode 1]
body:
So I just started watching Killing Eve (I’m only on episode one so no spoilers please) and I really love it.  

1) Great representation.  The main two characters are female; one is Asian/Canadian married to a Polish husband (Eve), the other is Eastern European and appears to be Bisexual Aromantic based on what I’ve seen so far (Villanelle)

2) Great acting, both the titular Eve and Villanelle are played as believable people and the latter definitely comes across as both complex but also simply psychopathic especially when she ropes that kid into part of her plan to assassinate the boy’s grandfather.  Also Kim Bodnia (Martin Rohde from The Bridge) is in it and that never hurts

3) Funny dialogue/great script.  Probably my favourite scene is where Eve ask so her husband how he would kill her in a hypothetical situation ““push you down the stairs” or “flattery” is his answer clearly taking it light heartedly before Eve describes very descriptively how she would kill him and dispose of his body and grins at the end like ““see? Isn’t that neat!”  Second favourite is where Villanelle casually offers hair advice to Eve before going on a four person murder spree down the hall.

4) The way it’s filmed/directed/edited.  Whatever it’s doing it’s working, it is both bizarre but intriguing in the way it’s presented to the viewer and I love it.

Definitely going to keep watching

summary: OK, I am so committed to watching Killing Eve as instructed that I have LEARNED TO TURN THE TV ON so I can watch the first...
body:
OK, I am so committed to watching Killing Eve as instructed that I have LEARNED TO TURN THE TV ON so I can watch the first episode as it’s broadcast (an hour from now). It did in fact only take me about three minutes to work out.

I previously knew how to make it run Netflix, but I can’t remember the last time I tried to watch something during its broadcast. (Ponder’s run the telly signal through a Magic Recording Box, so you have to be able to manipulate the Magic Recording Box in order to watch anything, you can’t just switch the TV on.)
